"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525691","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-27","<p>The Government is firmly committed to ensuring that the needs of transgender prisoners are fully met and their rights respected. The Ministry of Justice has carried out a review into the care and management of transgender offenders, which will be published in due course.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-06-27T08:51:40.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525691/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525691/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525691/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-15","Prisoners: Gender Recognition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will publish new guidance on assisting transgender people in prison.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","40689"
