"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525027","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-27","<p>Data on the representation status of defendants in the Crown Court is published as part of the annual Criminal Court Statistics publication at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-court-statistics-quarterly-january-to-march-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-court-statistics-quarterly-january-to-march-2015</a>. The representation status of defendants in magistrates’ courts is not recorded. Data on whether unrepresented defendants meet legal aid means and merits tests, and whether they chose to defend themselves, is not available.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","40570 ; 40571 ; 40572","2016-06-27T09:24:07.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525027/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525027/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525027/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-14","Legal Representation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many unrepresented defendants there were in the (a) magistrates' courts and (b) Crown courts.","false","Biography information for Christina Rees","Neath","Christina Rees","40573"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525028","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-27","<p>I refer the honourable member to the answer given to PQ 38292 on 02 June 2016.</p><p> </p><p>Reform prisons have unprecedented freedom over their regime and the rehabilitative services they provide, allowing their governors to innovate and run their prison as they see fit. We have put the tools to drive change in the hands of those at the frontline who know best what works. Governors are currently developing reform plans for their prisons. They are expected to tackle the most pressing challenges in their prisons which are likely to include many of these issues.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","40567","2016-06-27T09:11:06.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525028/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525028/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525028/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-14","Prisons: Reform","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what reforms have been put in place in the six early adopter reform prisons to tackle (a) self-harm, (b) prisoner on prisoner violence, (c) assaults on staff and (d) use of new psychoactive substances; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","40611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525029","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-27","<p>I refer the honourable member to the answer given to PQ 38292 on 02 June 2016.</p><p> </p><p>Reform prisons have unprecedented freedom over their regime and the rehabilitative services they provide, allowing their governors to innovate and run their prison as they see fit. We have put the tools to drive change in the hands of those at the frontline who know best what works. Governors are currently developing reform plans for their prisons. They are expected to tackle the most pressing challenges in their prisons which are likely to include many of these issues.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","40611","2016-06-27T09:11:06.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525029/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525029/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525029/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-14","Prisons: Reform","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will publish the criteria used to select the six early adopter reform prisons.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","40567"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525030","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-27","<p>The Bill was announced as part of legislative programme for this session in the Queen's speech. Further details on the timing of the Bill will be announced in due course.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-06-27T09:14:55.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525030/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525030/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525030/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-14","Prisons: Reform","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when he plans to publish the Prison Reform Bill.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","40568"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525031","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-30","<p>The information requested is published in the Criminal Justice System Statistics Quarterly, at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2015</a>. The maximum penalty for the offence is a fine not exceeding £1,000.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2016-06-30T09:52:44.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525031/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525031/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525031/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-14","Prostitution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many men have been found guilty of offences under Section 53A of the Sexual Offences Act 2003 as amended by Section 14 of the Policing and Crime Act 2009 since 1 April 2010; and what sentence was imposed in each such case.","false","Biography information for Fiona Mactaggart","Slough","Fiona Mactaggart","40623"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525032","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-27","<p>The Information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-06-27T09:18:11.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525032/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525032/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525032/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-14","Prisons: Arson","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the cost to the public purse was of repairs to cells and prisoner accommodation required because of acts of arson in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","40569"
