"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524621","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-06-27","<p>The Department holds a range of information relating to Universal Credit and housing but do not hold the information you have requested.</p>",,"Lord Freud","HL653","2016-06-27T14:31:24.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524621/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524621/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524621/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-06-13","Joint European Torus","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many of the Universal Credit claimants currently in rent arrears did not have a record of being behind with their payments before moving to Universal Credit.","false","Biography information for Baroness Manzoor",,"Baroness Manzoor","HL654"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524622","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-06-27","<p>The payment arrangements for Universal Credit are designed to help reduce welfare dependency by mirroring the world of work, in which 75 per cent of employees are paid monthly. Appropriate budgeting support is available to ensure recipients are supported effectively.</p>",,"Lord Freud",,"2016-06-27T14:30:55.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524622/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524622/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524622/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-06-13","Gaza: Politics and Government","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to undertake a review of the impact of the policy by which Universal Credit is paid monthly in arrears.","false","Biography information for Baroness Manzoor",,"Baroness Manzoor","HL655"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524623","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-06-22","<p>The Heritage Lottery Fund work closely to support grant recipients in meeting the essential requirements prior to works starting. The HLF are not aware of a general problem with delays around the existing permission to start process, though timings can vary.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2016-06-22T11:14:02.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524623/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524623/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524623/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-06-13","Hamas","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they are taking to reduce the delays that occur between the announcement of a Heritage Lottery Fund grant being made and permission to start being given to the recipient organisations.","true","Biography information for Lord Smith of Finsbury",,"Lord Smith of Finsbury","HL656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524624","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-27","<p>In relation to UK law civil and criminal proceedings cannot be taken against the Sovereign as a person under UK law.</p><p><br>Under EU law, EU Heads of State enjoy a special status, in accordance with generally accepted principles of international law.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2016-06-27T17:01:08.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524624/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524624/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524624/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-13","Gaza: Ports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the Sovereign is subject to legislation originating in the EU.","false","Biography information for Lord Tebbit",,"Lord Tebbit","HL657"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524625","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-27","<p>There is an income tax deduction available where an employer provides corporate uniforms, or where an employee must purchase such clothing. To be considered a uniform clothing must meet certain criteria. The clothing must be: specialised, recognisable as a uniform and intended to identify its wearer as having a particular occupation. These requirements ensure that the tax deduction is used as intended.</p><p> </p><p>No assessment has been made of how many corporate uniforms in the UK could be diverted from landfill or incineration if these tax rules were changed. No assessment has been made of the financial implications of changing these taxation requirements.</p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley","HL659 ; HL660","2016-06-27T12:20:45.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524625/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524625/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524625/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-13","Gaza: Fentanyl","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of how many corporate uniforms in the UK could be diverted from landfill or incineration if the tax regime relating to permanent branding were changed.","false","Biography information for Baroness Young of Hornsey",,"Baroness Young of Hornsey","HL658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524626","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-27","<p>There is an income tax deduction available where an employer provides corporate uniforms, or where an employee must purchase such clothing. To be considered a uniform clothing must meet certain criteria. The clothing must be: specialised, recognisable as a uniform and intended to identify its wearer as having a particular occupation. These requirements ensure that the tax deduction is used as intended.</p><p> </p><p>No assessment has been made of how many corporate uniforms in the UK could be diverted from landfill or incineration if these tax rules were changed. No assessment has been made of the financial implications of changing these taxation requirements.</p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley","HL658 ; HL660","2016-06-27T12:20:45.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524626/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524626/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524626/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-13","Gaza","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the financial implications of changing taxation requirements to replace permanent branding on corporate uniforms with non-permanent branding.","false","Biography information for Baroness Young of Hornsey",,"Baroness Young of Hornsey","HL659"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524627","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-27","<p>There is an income tax deduction available where an employer provides corporate uniforms, or where an employee must purchase such clothing. To be considered a uniform clothing must meet certain criteria. The clothing must be: specialised, recognisable as a uniform and intended to identify its wearer as having a particular occupation. These requirements ensure that the tax deduction is used as intended.</p><p> </p><p>No assessment has been made of how many corporate uniforms in the UK could be diverted from landfill or incineration if these tax rules were changed. No assessment has been made of the financial implications of changing these taxation requirements.</p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley","HL658 ; HL659","2016-06-27T12:20:45.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524627/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524627/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524627/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-13","Surrogate Motherhood: Lone Parents","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what are the barriers to amending taxation requirements so that the permanent branding on corporate uniforms could be replaced with non-permanent branding.","false","Biography information for Baroness Young of Hornsey",,"Baroness Young of Hornsey","HL660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524628","Department for Education","false","2016-06-27","<p>The Government is currently assessing the full impact that the General Data Protection Regulation will have on individual areas of data processing. Certain provisions of the Regulation will have direct effect in UK law, including a continuing right of access for data subjects to their personal data and other information. In certain areas, the regulation leaves the option for domestic legislation to restrict rights that arise under it in certain circumstances (article 23).</p><p>The Regulation will apply from 25 May 2018. Before then, the Department for Education will assess whether the current statutory guidance covering care leavers’ access to their case records needs to be revised.</p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2016-06-27T15:15:45.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524628/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524628/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524628/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-13","Care Leavers: Personal Records","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their assessment of the impact the General Data Protection Regulation (Regulation (EU) 2016/679) will have on care leavers’ full access to their care records.","false","Biography information for Baroness Young of Hornsey",,"Baroness Young of Hornsey","HL661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524629","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-27","<p>The Government recognises that there are some intrinsic inequalities within the courtesy titles system as it relates to honorifics. We have sympathy with those who are seeking to resolve such inequalities and we are looking into the process around courtesy titles, including in relation to same sex spouses and civil partners. The resolution of these inequalities is a very complex issue and we are at an early stage. We will provide an update in due course.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2016-06-27T15:53:18.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524629/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524629/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524629/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-13","High Speed 2 Railway Line","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the answer given by Baroness Chisholm of Owlpen on 9 June (HL Deb, col 817), how the consideration of honorary titles for the spouses of women members of the House of Lords will be conducted; whether same sex spouses and civil partners will be included in the exercise; and when that exercise will be completed.","false","Biography information for Lord Lexden",,"Lord Lexden","HL662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524635","Home Office","false","2016-06-27","<p>The Home Office does not hold data centrally on the morale of police officers. It is the responsibility of chief officers - supported by the College of Policing - to ensure good management systems are in place to support officers in their work. It is ultimately a matter for chief constables and police and crime commissioners to monitor the morale and engagement levels of their workforce.</p><p>The Government recognises the importance of police welfare- in October 2014 we allocated £10m to help support emergency services personnel and volunteers, focused on mental health, physical recuperation and bereavement support for those who need it.</p><p>£4m was allocated to the charity Mind specifically for mental health issues to cover financial years 2014/15 and 2015/16.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-06-27T12:01:31.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524635/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524635/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524635/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-13","Police: Job Satisfaction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent assessment she has made of the morale of police officers (a) nationally and (b) at force level; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","40270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524636","Home Office","false","2016-06-27","<p>The Government?s reforms to policing are designed to create a more capable, flexible and professional workforce. Central to these reforms was the establishment of the College of Policing as the professional body for policing, charged with setting standards and further professionalising the police.</p><p>Recruitment to the police is managed within a national application, assessment and selection framework maintained by the College. Within this remit the College is delivering a number of major pieces of work including a review of initial police recruitment, proposals for a new police educational qualification framework and implementing the recommendations of its 2014 Leadership Review.</p><p>These reforms, along with innovative schemes such as Direct Entry and Police Now, focus on recognising and developing the skills of existing officers, as well as ensuring that policing can continue to attract the brightest and best new recruits.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-06-27T12:35:24.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524636/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524636/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524636/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-13","Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking to (a) attract, recruit and retain high-quality police officers and (b) offer such officers career development.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","40271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524637","Home Office","false","2016-06-27","<p>Decisions on the size, composition and deployment of a police force's workforce are operational matters for individual chief constables, working with their Police and Crime Commissioners.</p><p>HMIC's progress report on the police response to domestic abuse, published in December 2015, found that forces have continued largely to protect their dedicated teams or other resources that focus on public protection work.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-06-27T12:32:39.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524637/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524637/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524637/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-13","Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment has been made of the adequacy of staffing levels in Police Public Protection Units at (a) UK and (b) force level.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","40272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524638","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-27","<p>The Apprenticeship Grant for Employers (AGE) is available until the end of the 2016/17 academic year to incentivise smaller employers to offer apprenticeships. The AGE grant will be devolved to The Tees Valley Combined Authority from this August. They will be free to vary the criteria associated with the grant (e.g. size and sector of business) to meet local needs.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-06-27T16:10:47.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524638/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524638/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524638/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-13","Apprentices: Tees Valley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the report by Lord Heseltine, entitled Tees Valley: opportunity unlimited, published in June 2016, recommendation 6.6.7, whether he plans to devolve responsibility for the Apprenticeship Grant for Employers to the Tees Valley Combined Authority.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","40293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524639","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-20","<p>The Department does not produce forecasts for apprenticeship starts. Apprenticeships are paid jobs and their availability is dependent on employers offering opportunities and hiring apprentices.</p><p>The levy will fund a step-change in apprenticeship numbers and quality – delivering on our commitment to 3 million new apprenticeship starts in England by 2020. It will put apprenticeship funding on a sustainable footing and improve the technical and professional skills of the workforce.</p><p>It will encourage employers to invest in their apprentices and take on more. Employers in England who pay the levy and are committed to apprenticeships training will be able to get out more than they pay in to the levy through a top-up of additional funding to their digital accounts. The government will apply a 10% top-up to monthly funds entering levy paying employers digital accounts, for apprenticeship training in England, from April 2017. Apprentices who have been accepted on to an apprenticeship before April 2017 will be funded for the full term of the apprenticeship under the terms and conditions that were in place at the time their apprenticeship started.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-06-20T14:07:29.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524639/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524639/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524639/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-13","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the new Apprenticeship Levy on the number of apprenticeship start-ups from September 2016.","false","Biography information for Karen Lumley","Redditch","Karen Lumley","40284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524640","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-27","<p>My Department is currently developing the policy detail to be included within the consultation, which we plan to publish later this year. I am not able to commit to a specific date for the consultation at this point.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-06-27T08:22:51.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524640/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524640/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524640/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-13","Property: Ownership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 3 June 2016 to Question 37744, on property: ownership, on what date (a) his Department will begin to consult on the detail of the policy and (b) that consultation will end.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","40364"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524641","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-20","<p>The Department has not made a specific forecast of how many jobs will be replaced (or how many additional jobs will be created) over the next two decades due to automation. However, the Government’s Horizon Scanning Programme exploring the impacts of automation on the labour market, and engaging with our international partners.</p><p>Government is taking action to provide individuals with the skills that will help prepare them for changes to the labour market, such as the new school computing curriculum, developing new apprenticeship standards, growing the apprenticeships programme, and introducing the Institute for Coding.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-06-20T14:08:26.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524641/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524641/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524641/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-13","Automation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether his Department has made an estimate of the potential number of jobs which will be replaced by automation over the next two decades.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","40325"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524642","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-27","<p>The Student Loans Company will open for applications for the new master’s loan for postgraduate study from the end of June 2016 and the Department has been working closely with the company to ensure its systems and operational staff are ready to manage the loan’s administration.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-06-27T08:25:24.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524642/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524642/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524642/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-13","Postgraduate Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the operational readiness of the Student Loans Company to administer postgraduate loan applications between June and October 2016.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","40420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524643","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-27","<p>There is a dedicated enquiry line for applicants for the new master’s loan for postgraduate study. The number is 0300 100 0031 and the line is open Monday to Friday from 8am to 6pm.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-06-27T08:28:27.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524643/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524643/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524643/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-13","Postgraduate Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether a dedicated hotline for postgraduate loan applicants will be established by the Student Loans Company.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","40421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524644","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-27","<p>The Department’s current central estimate is that around 60,000 students will take out the new postgraduate master’s loan in Academic Year 2016/17. We estimate that a similar number of students will take out the loan in each of the Academic Years 2017/18 and 2018/19. These estimates will be reviewed in light of the student applications received in the first year of the loan’s operation. The new master’s loan will be available to eligible students including those UK students ordinarily resident in England or EU nationals resident elsewhere in the EU who meet the loan’s eligibility criteria. As this is a new loan product this year, it is too early to give an accurate estimate of the domicile of borrowers in 2017/18 or 2018/19.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-06-27T08:33:26.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524644/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524644/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524644/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-13","Postgraduate Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of the expected take-up of postgraduate loans by (a) UK and (b) EU students in (i) 2017-18 and (ii) 2018-19; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","40422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524645","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-27","<p>The Student Loans Company will open applications for the new master’s loan for postgraduate study from the end of June 2016. Around 40 additional full-time equivalent staff will support the new loan product.</p><p> </p><p>The additional staff will be required to process the applications, administer the payment of student loans and deal with any enquiries from students in relation to the new product.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-06-27T08:44:00.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524645/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524645/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/524645/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-13","Postgraduate Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of the additional staffing and resources required by the Student Loans Company for administration and postgraduate loan applications from October 2016.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","40423"
